subject: San Jacinto College Bid Opportunity Invitation: RFP #26-05 (College Wide Copier Lease and Maintenance Program)
body_text: Dear Supplier,  A new event matching your commodity registration profile is available.  San Jacinto College   Bid Opportunity Information  Bid Number: RFP #26-05 Bid Title: College Wide Copier Lease and Maintenance Program Issue Date: 9/25/2025 08:03:00 AM (CT) Close Date: 10/16/2025 02:00:00 PM (CT) Question Cut Off Date: 10/7/2025 05:00:00 PM (CT)   Bid Notes   The San Jacinto Community College District (SJCCD or College) is seeking sealed proposals from qualified firms to provide College Wide Copier Lease and Maintenance Program services.         All proposals must be submitted through this IonWave e-Bidding system. The system does    not    allow proposals to be submitted unless   all requirements have been met   such as responses to required Attributes and uploaded required Attachments. This takes time to complete, so please   do not wait   to submit your proposal.      There are eight tabs to our solicitations:  1.  Event Details : Contains the issue date and time, close date and time, status of the request, notes, and contact information for the Buyer.  2.  Questions : Submit any questions you may have before the deadline. See Activities tab for deadlines.  3.  Activities : Any event dates related to this solicitation.  4.  Attachments : Read all attachments. Scope of work, specifications, proposal format requirements, etc. can be found here.  5.  Attributes :  Acknowledgements, terms and conditions, questions about your firm, references, etc.   6.  Line Items : Read about the specified item(s) and enter pricing, discount, or other information requested.  7.  Response Attachments : Attach all required documents and information.  8.  Response Submission :  Enter the name and e-mail address of respondent and submit response. This individual must have the authority to submit a response on the company's behalf.        Bid Contact Information  Farrah Khalil 4620 Fairmont Parkway A2.208 Pasadena, TX 77504 USA 1 (281) 998-6326  Uni  farrah.khalil@sjcd.edu   Click Here to View Opportunity   Questions about this system can be directed to: San Jacinto College   Unsubscribe        VNDBIDAUTOINVITE - 9/25/2025 08:05 AM (CT)

subject: 529601538, BroadAxis, Inc., Ross Clark, Applications Architect 3
body_text: HHSC/ DIR Review Team,        Please find attached the resume submission of  Ross Clark  for the position  Applications Architect 3  position as part of Solicitation  529601538 .      Professional Summary:      Ross Clark is a highly qualified candidate with over  20 years of GIS leadership experience , including more than 15 years at the  City of Austin , where he directed one of the largest municipal GIS programs in Texas. He brings deep expertise in  Esri ArcGIS Enterprise architecture, SQL Server Enterprise Geodatabases, Python scripting, and SQL development , with proven success in managing large-scale data migrations (Utility Network, ArcGIS Pro), governance frameworks, and QA/QC standards. Ross has extensive experience leading enterprise projects, supervising large teams, and managing multi-million-dollar budgets, making him well-suited for the Applications Architect 3 role. He has background in  data governance, enterprise standards, and stakeholder engagement across government and utilities .          The submission includes the following documents, merged into a single PDF as per your guidelines:      Candidate Qualification Form  Candidate Resume  Candidate Reference Form  Candidate Acknowledgement Form   We have also verified the candidate’s compliance with all specified requirements and signed agreements as noted in the solicitation.          Please feel free to reach out if you need any additional information or documentation.             Regards,               Sidra Malik   Manager, IT Staffing   BroadAxis, Inc. subject: Texas Health and Human Services Commission has posted Solicitation Number 529601538 to the DIR ITSAC Portal
body_text:
Texas Health and Human Services Commission has posted a new ITSAC Solicitation to the ITSAC Portal. Respondents must submit all questions regarding the documents and/or requirements contained within this solicitation to the point of contact listed below or the point of contact identified by the solicitation documents. DIR is not able to provide any insight or clarification regarding DIR customer entity posted solicitations.

Please review all documentation posted in the portal thoroughly for any unique instructions on response requirements.  If you would like to respond please go to: https://dir.my.site.com/itsacvendor/s/itsac-vendor-response/a58cs00000EN31DAAT.

SOLICITATION DETAILS

Solicitation Number: 529601538

Customer Name: Texas Health and Human Services Commission

Solicitation Point of Contact: it_staff_aug@hhsc.state.tx.us

Response Due Date: Deadline Date: October 7, 2025 at 5PM (CST)


If your company is interested in submitting a response to the agency’s procurement, you must submit the response directly to Texas Health and Human Services Commission’s point of contact or in whatever manner is specified by the solicitation by the response due date and time. Resumes cannot be submitted to the customer entity through the ITSAC Portal or through DIR.

Please contact dirstaffaugmentation@dir.texas.gov if you are experiencing system errors and cannot view the solicitation documents.
